<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-19704] UnsupportedOperationException is thrown when no space for LCS</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19704</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;CompactionTask#buildCompactionCandidatesForAvailableDiskSpace&lt;/tt&gt; with LCS, if node has limited disk space and can&apos;t remove any sstable from L0 or L1 in &lt;tt&gt;LeveledCompactionTask#reduceScopeForLimitedSpace&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;LeveledCompactionTask#partialCompactionsAcceptable&lt;/tt&gt; will throw &lt;tt&gt;UnsupportedOperationException&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should handle &lt;tt&gt;LeveledCompactionTask#partialCompactionsAcceptable&lt;/tt&gt; more gracefully with &lt;tt&gt;return level &amp;lt;= 1&lt;/tt&gt; or simply &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt; since &lt;tt&gt;reduceScopeForLimitedSpace&lt;/tt&gt; only removes sstable from L0 or L1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Related &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17272&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17272&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
